A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending the Henry County Office of the Solicitor-General; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Henry County Office of the Solicitor-General is responsible for prosecuting
4 misdemeanor crimes on behalf of the State of Georgia and the citizens of Henry County; and
5 WHEREAS, the Victim Services Division of the Henry County Office of the
6 Solicitor-General is designed to assist crime victims throughout the various stages of the
7 judicial process; and
8 WHEREAS, each case involving a victim is assigned to a victim advocate within the Henry
9 County Office of the Solicitor-General who ensures that victims are informed of their rights,
10 provided with available resources, and given additional assistance as needed; and
11 WHEREAS, in 2024, the Victim Services Division of the Henry County Office of the
12 Solicitor-General provided assistance to approximately 975 victims affected by misdemeanor
13 criminal cases; and
