14 WHEREAS, February 5, 2025, marks Stand With Survivors Day at the state capitol, a day
15 dedicated to raising awareness and advocating for the rights and safety of domestic violence
16 survivors; and
17 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable office be appropriately
18 honored during this special time.
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
20 the members of this body recognize and commend the Henry County Office of the
21 Solicitor-General for its dedicated, effective, and efficient service on behalf of those in need
22 as well as extend sincere best wishes for continued success.
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
24 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
25 Henry County Office of the Solicitor-General.
